HEADWORD: Siphonet
<hw>Si"phon*et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the two dorsal tubular organs on the hinder part of the
abdomen of aphids. They give exit to the honeydew. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Aphis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siphonia</ent>⟦br⟧
